headline: "Taft Union High School, Taft, CA",
text: "Jan 10, 2013 â€“ A 16-year-old student in Southern California set out to shoot two other students who had bullied him. The unnamed student came armed to Taft Union High School with a 12-gauge shotgun early January. One student was shot in the chest and sustained non-life-threatening injuries while the second target was shot at but got away unscathed. A year earlier, the shooter was suspended for compiling a "hit list". Many students described the shooter as a loner who was called names. If it were not for science teacher Ryan Heber, 41, who talked the young shooter into putting the gun down, more students may have been harmed."
