headline: "University of Central Florida, Orlando, FL",
text: "Mar 18, 2013 â€“ The University of Central Florida had a "close call" with a student gunman on its campus March of last year. Police reported, James Oliver Seevakumaran, 30, made a checklist to execute a mass murder that included instructions like "pull fire alarm" and "give them hell". Seevakumaran pulled the fire alarm in his dormitory with the hopes of causing panic and having all the students gather in the halls. His roommate, Arabo Babkhani, said the quiet gunman never made eye-contact with him until the day of the event where Seevakumaran held a gun to Babkhani's face. Babkhani immediately locked himself in the bathroom to call police. When police arrived they found that Seevakumaran had shot himself along with a .45-caliber semi-automatic pistol, a .22-caliber tactical rifle, ammunition and a backpack with four homemade explosive devices."
},
