headline: "New River Community College, Christiansburg, VA",
text: "Apr 12, 2013 â€“ An 18-year-old college student, Neil Allan MacInnis, faces two counts of malicious wounding and use of a firearm in the commission of a felony after shooting and injuring two women at a mall. MacInnis was a student at the New River Community College and opened fire at the school's satellite campus, the New River Valley Mall. The type of weapon he used or how it was obtained has not been released because of the ongoing investigations. The Christiansburg Police Department police chief said MacInnis participated in the Christiansburg Police Department Citizens Academy program in 2012. The free program is a 12-week course where citizens can observe the department on a regular day, get the opportunity to ride along in police cars, tour the offices and practice with firearms at the shooting range."
