headline: "Santa Monica College, Santa Monica, CA",
text: "Jun 7, 2013 - â€œAnytime someone puts on a vest, comes out with a bag full of loaded magazines, has a hand gun, has a semi-automatic rifle, and car-jacks folks, goes to a college, kills more people, I would say that thatâ€™s premeditated.â€ This was police chief Jacqueline Seabrooks' perspective of what happened on that day.<br><br>It was only a year ago that the Santa Monica College experienced an unexpected attack of terror. Last June, John Zawahri, a former student of the SMC, shot and killed five, and injured several. The spree of violence began just before noon at the gunman's home, where the 23-year-old killed his own father and brother, and lit the familyâ€™s house ablaze. Zawahri then hi-jacked a nearby car, and demanded the driver, an adult woman, take him to Santa Monica College. Along the way, he opened fire on another woman driving by and also a city bus. The woman and three bus passengers were injured. As the shooter approached the campus, he fired at Carlos Navarro Franco, a groundskeeper at the school, who died instantly. Franco's passenger, daughter Marcela, was rushed to Ronald Reagan UCLA Medical Center in West Los Angeles, where she passed away a day later. En route to the school's library entrance, Zawahri gunned down an unidentified adult woman in her 50s. When entering the library, the shooter fired over 70 rounds of gun shots, There, he was shot and killed by police."
},
