headline: "Ronald E. McNair Discovery Learning Academy, Decatur, GA",
text: "Aug 20, 2013 â€“ Michael Brandon Hill, 20, was taken into custody after he fired six rounds of gun shots in the main office of the McNair Discovery Learning Academy on August 20th 2013. Prior to surrendering, Hill told bookkeeper Antoinette Tuff, that he was mentally unstable, and had nothing to live for. Hill was charged with aggravated assault on a police officer, terroristic threats, and possession of a firearm by a convicted felon. The gunmanâ€™s brother, Tim, considered Michael a dangerous individual, telling NBC News that his brother â€œwas bipolar and suffered from ADD.â€ Hill was questioned by police for hours, but his motive remained unclear. Officials are also unsure whether or not Hill had ties to the school. No one was injured. In December 2013, Hill was classified as mentally unable to stand trial, and entered a plea of mental incompetence."
},
