headline: "Sparks Middle School, Sparks, NV",
text: "Oct 21, 2013 â€“ When the parents of a young boy sent their child off to school last fall, they thought it would be an ordinary school day. What they didn't think was that the boy had their Ruger 9mm pistol tucked away in his backpack.<br><br>The 12-year-old student arrived on the grounds of Sparks Middle School, armed and dangerous. Shortly before 7:15AM, the boy shot a student in the shoulder, wounding him. He then continued toward the basketball court, where he shot and killed Michael Landsberry, a math teacher at the school. The boyâ€™s violent streak ended when he fatally shot himself in the head. The shooter never entered the building and no shots were fired by law enforcement.<br><br>Two students were rushed to a local hospital, and both were in stable condition later that day. Officials say the boy obtained the gun from his parents. While his motive remains unknown, a Sparks student, Michelle Hernandez, told the Reno Gazette-Journal that the shooter had complained about being teased.<br><br>â€œI heard him saying, 'Why you people making fun of me, why you laughing at me'â€, she said."
},
