headline: "Arapahoe High School, Centennial, CO",
text: "Dec 13, 2013 â€“ Karl Pierson, 18, entered Arapahoe High School equipped with a shot gun, a machete, 125 rounds of ammunition, and 3 Molotov cocktails.<br><br>Prior to the shooting, Pierson went bowling - a chilling connection to the Columbine High School shooting years earlier; shooters, students Eric Harris and Dylan Klebold were alleged to have attended a bowling class hours before their attack.<br><br>After bowling, Pierson purchased more ammunition. Arapahoe County Sheriff Grayson Robinson said, â€œthere is no question that this was a very deliberate and planned eventâ€ He also said the teen was likely motivated by a dispute with his debate coach, Tracy Murphy. Murphy was believed to be the gunman's intended target.<br><br>Upon arrival at the school, Pierson entered through a door that was normally locked. He fired his first shot randomly in the schoolâ€™s hallway, then his second, killing 17-year-old Claire Esther Davis of the senior class. He fired another blow before entering the schoolâ€™s library and media center. According to Robinson, Pierson fired a third shot in the area outside the office of the school librarian and Murphy. He then ignited a Molotov cocktail in the center of the library, causing a destructive fire. With his fifth and final shot, he took his own life, shooting himself in the head."
},
