headline: "Berrendo Middle School, Roswell, NM",
text: "Jan 14, 2014 â€“ A 12-year-old boy pulled a sawed-off shotgun from his bag and fired shots in a New Mexico Middle School gymnasium. According to authorities, the unnamed 7th grade shooter opened fire in the schoolâ€™s gym with a 20-gauge shotgun, killing one student and seriously injuring 2 others. Two children: an 11 year-old-boy, and a 13-year-old girl were flown to University Medical Center, TX. that morning. The girl, who had been identified as Kendal Sanders, was wounded in the shoulder. The boy, who was not identified at the request of his family, was severely wounded in his face and neck, but later listed as stable. John Masterson, an 8th grade social studies teacher, approached the shooter and talked him into laying down the weapon. New Mexico State Police Chief Pete Kassetas, said investigators were serving three search warrants, but would not say where they were being served or what charges the student may face."
},
