headline: "Seattle Pacific University, Seattle, WA",
text: "Jun 5, 2014 - The man responsible for the Seattle Pacific University shootings at the beginning of June was off his psychosis medication because he "wanted to feel the hate". Aaron Rey Ybarra, 26, was not a student at the university and police reported he had done extensive research on other mass shootings, like Columbine, in order to carry out his own. After firing a few rounds, one 19-year-old was pronounced dead at the hospital and two students were injured.Ybarra was armed with a shotgun, a knife and nearly 50 shells of ammunition with intentions to attack a mass number of students and taking his own life before a student security guard subdued the shooter with pepper spray. After being arrested, Ybarra gave police an hour long interview where he said he didn't specifically target anyone but had a "hatred for the world in general"."
},
