headline: "Reynolds High School, Troutdale, OR",
text: "Jun 10, 2014 â€“ Parents of 15-year-old gunman, Jared Michael Padgett, were "confused and shocked" when they found out their son was the suspected killer in the school shootings at an Oregonian high school leaving one student dead. The shooter concealed his weapons, a AR-15 type rifle, a semi-automatic handgun, a knife and hundreds of rounds of ammunition, in a backpack and guitar case. After arriving to Reynolds High School that Tuesday morning, Padgett went to the school's gym and began shooting. He managed to kill 14-year-old student athlete, Emilio Hoffman before chasing psychical education teacher, Todd Rispler down the hall while shooting. Rispler managed to escape while injured and initiated a lockdown. When officers arrived to the school, they engaged Padgett in a gun battle before the gunman took his own life in a school bathroom."
},
